			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2009</a> keynote:</span><br><i>If MDE Is the Solution, Then What Is the Problem?</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JeanBézivín.html">Jean Bézivín</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_2">10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_2</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagM">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> Keynote positions model-driven engineering within a broader software-language-engineering context and critiques mismatches between problems and proposed MDE solutions.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> It reflects on the role of meta-level descriptions (models/metamodels) in MDE as a foundational concern.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It touches on how MDE tooling ecosystems shape what problems can practically be addressed.
</li></ul></li></ul>
